  <description><![CDATA[<p>The charming Hotel Betulla is lovingly run by Luca, Oscar and Vittorio. The team offer a warm welcome and a friendly face after a day on the slopes and serve up delicious food to keep you fuelled every day. </p>
<h2>Alpine style</h2>
<p>Each of the rooms in the hotel is unique in design, furnished in a cosy alpine style, and are equipped with all of the modern conveniences needed for a week skiing in <a data-udi="umb://document/ea59b48ae29b417b81f9c9850d58d038" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ea59b48ae29b417b81f9c9850d58d038}" title="Madonna Di Campiglio" data-anchor="#">Madonna Di Campiglio.</a> Plus many of the rooms benefit from having views of the surrounding mountains and the resort. </p>
<p>Fuel up for a day on the slopes at the varied breakfast buffet, and return to a tasty three course evening meal. Once a week you can enjoy a typical Trentino style dinner where you can taste local food and drink from the region.</p>
<h2>Good location</h2>
<p>Located towards the entrance of <span>Madonna di Campiglio, the Hotel Betulla enjoys a quiet location away from the centre of the resort. It is really easy to get onto the slopes each day, the Pinzolo-Campiglio Express is just two minutes' walk from the hotel. </span></p>
<p><span>In and around the pretty resort centre you can find a variety of different restaurants, cafes and shops - most often serving and selling Italian produce.</span></p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Hotel Betulla the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>]]></description>
